          <h3>The Vacancy Clause Problem</h3>
          <p>Most standard homeowner insurance policies in Ontario contain a vacancy clause. If your home sits unoccupied for more than 30 to 60 consecutive days, your coverage is reduced or voided entirely. A vacant home during a Canadian winter is an insurer's nightmare: frozen pipes, undetected leaks, and no one to call emergency services.</p>

          <p>Here's the irony: renting your home while you're away actually solves the vacancy problem. An occupied home maintains coverage. But you must notify your insurer that you're renting, because standard homeowner policies typically don't cover rental activity either.</p>

